<item>
            <title>[SOLR-654] Modify the solrj SolrResponse API so responses can be dynamicaly constructed and loaded.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-654</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current SolrResponse implementations put most of their logic within a class specific constructor.  This makes it difficult to dynamically build and populate a SolrResponse via reflection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch removes the NamedList&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt; from most constructors and puts it into a method: setResponse( NamedList )&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
